  "commentary": "With SPX at 6597.76 sitting between the max negative gamma at 6590 (-10.6B) and max positive gamma at 6605 (+15.9B), dealers are in a critical hedging zone where they're likely buying the current level as spot hovers just above the amplifying 6590 support. The massive +15.9B gamma wall at 6605 will trigger heavy dealer selling if we push higher, creating significant resistance, while a break below 6590 would force dealers into accelerated selling that could drive momentum toward the 6580 level. The GEX surge event combined with spot trading below the 6702 flip in PIN regime suggests dealers are actively hedging around these tight 6590-6605 bounds.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pinned between 6590 and 6605 with choppy action.",
